HEADWORD: Courche
<hw>Courche</hw> <pr>(k??rsh)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Kerchief</er>.]</ety> <def>A square piece of linen used formerly by
women instead of a cap; a kerchief.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>curch</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

